==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Methylene
<hw>Meth"yl*ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧thyl⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>, from Gr. <?/ wine + <?/ wood; -- a
word coined to correspond to the name <ets>wood spirit</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A divalent hydrocarbon radical,
<chform>-CH2-</chform>, not known in the free state, but regarded as an
essential residue and component of certain derivatives of methane;
<as>as, <ex>methylene</ex> bromide, <chform>CH2Br2</chform></as>; --
formerly called also <altname>methene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Methylene blue</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>an
artificial dyestuff consisting of a complex sulphur derivative of
diphenyl amine; -- called also <altname>pure
blue</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>methylenedioxymethamphetamine</ent>⟦br⟧
